Steps to add a file in GIT :-

1. Create a file in working repository.
2. Go to working repository in terminal.
3. To see your changes/insertion in local repository use following command : git status
4. To add a file in repository, use following command : git add <file_name>. If you want to add multiple files at a same time then use command like this : git add <file_name1> <file_name2>
5. Commit the files that you've staged in your local repository: git commit -m "Message"
6. Push the changes in your local repository to GitHub: git push
                      
                      OR



